args:
Valentine's is nearing its end, and the group
reflects on the memories they've made.
When the prince acknowledges all the fine
feelings they've shared, the celebration ends
with a hearty ＂Happy Valentine's＂!

Everyone's been running around doing
exciting stuff and being nervous and
getting beat-up or whatever, sooo...yeah!
Seems like it was a good one.
I know I had a great time this year.\nThose apples really hit the spot!
Plus, we all ran around for the sake of a\ncommon goal, which is always fun.
It really did bring us closer together.
But we also had our fair share of\nhead-butting. ...Didn't we, Hildegarde?
And I apologize again for that.
I'm just glad to learn even a\nstick-in-the-mud like you has\na cute side!
Let us not get carried away.
When Valentine's is over, I will be back to\nprotecting order and ensuring pure, chaste\nliving among all who exist in this castle.
Clad in a dress or not, Hildegarde remains\nundeterred from her principles.
Ah, but this dignified stoicism of hers\nis also incredibly lovely...
Are you suggesting I would pursue any\nwoman who wandered into my gaze?\nPerish the very thought.
I seek only the honor of partaking in a\nserious relationship with everyone here!
I can't tell if that's actually kind of sweet\nor just suuuper creepy.
And Prometheus? Is there anything\nyou wish to share with the class?
Like perhaps the story of how you\nattempted to steal my darling from\nme, you dirty homewrecker?!
It seems this holiday has helped you\ngrow accustomed to things here\nat the Halidom, Prometheus.
This means I have a new rival now—\nwhich is COMPLETELY unacceptable.
It doesn't help that this new rival is\nso very attractive...
You guys all need to stow the inferiority\ncomplexes and just get along!
Seriously! You can't blame him for\nlooking so cool!
Do you think we made our feelings\nclear to His Highness?
We were all just talking about Valentine's.
So how'd it go? Do you know how much\nwe all love ya now, or what?
Would it kill you to learn a bit of\nsubtlety and tact, Luca?!
Soft, Elisanne. The feelings we each hold\nfor the prince take their own forms.
But everyone does hold you dear\nto their hearts in some fashion.
We have all made the depths of our\nfeelings known to you, yes?
Great! Now we can move on to\nthe next step: you, me, and\neverlasting exclusivity!
Oh just let me have this! \nValentine's is almost over!
It's my final push—there's no room\nfor subtlety!
*sigh* Do as you wish. \nBut pray do not lose focus.
For starting tomorrow, new days of\nstruggle await.
You mean when we struggle over our\nlove for the prince? Ha! You will LOSE!
You really must learn to take things\na bit more seriously.
Okay now, that's enough fighting!\nLet's end this one together. Ready?
Oh man, I can't wait for next year!
